cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on unsupervised representation learning using videos without semantic labels. The paper also proposes a convolutional neural network-based approach to learn rich and generalizable visual representation. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses a proxy task to learn the representation and validates the effectiveness of the learned representation using pre-training on high-level recognition problems. 

The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a novel approach to unsupervised representation learning using a sequence sorting task. 

The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses a convolutional neural network to sort the shuffled sequences and extract features from all frame pairs. 

Finally, the paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it uses videos as input and validates the effectiveness of the learned representation on action recognition, image classification, and object detection tasks.
